The paper discusses a family of alternative estimators that maximize a stochastic variation of the composite likelihood function. The paper also discusses experimental results in the context of Boltzmann machines and conditional random fields. These topics are typically associated with machine learning and statistical inference, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.ST (Statistics). The paper also discusses computational complexity, which is covered by the sub-categories cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
